title: Who has the edge? Houston Texans at Miami Dolphins
text:
Caption When the Dolphins run Weston Kenney / AP 
RB Lamar Miller (56 carries, 244 yards, 1 TD) got his game going last week against Tennessee. And the Dolphins rushed for a season-best 180 yards as LT Branden Albert, C Mike Pouncey (51) and the two-TE offense led the way. The key, however, might be that the Dolphins got an early lead against the Titans. If they trail against Houston it’ll be interesting to see if they stay committed to the run. The Texans, led by DT Vince Wilfork and ILB Brian Cushing, are physical. But they’re a mediocre 17th in the NFL against the run (109 yards per game). EDGE: DOLPHINS

EDGE: DOLPHINS (Weston Kenney / AP) Caption When the Texans run Phelan M. Ebenhack / AP 
RB Arian Foster (45 carries, 104 yards, 2.3 yards per carry) is back but he hasn’t yet rounded into form. RB Alfred Blue (57 carries, 226 yards, 4.0 yards per carry) had a 139-yard performance against Tampa Bay. But the Dolphins, who allowed just 63 yards rushing to Tennessee last week, think they might have found their run defense. DT Ndamukong Suh had a good showing last week as did LBs Koa Misi and Jelani Jenkins. Still, it takes more than one good showing to be convinced about this unit. The Dolphins are 31st in run defense (141 yards per game) while Houston is 23rd in rushing offense (96 yards per game). EDGE: TEXANS
